  "text": "SCFA (acetic, propionic and butyric acids) are among the major anions in colonic contents. They are found to a limited extent in the diet but are primarily produced in the proximal colon by anaerobic bacterial fermentation of dietary carbohydrates such as pectin [CITATION_1] ).",
